      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 static compression-bending configuration only. No variation in load angle, offset distance, or dynamic loading was included. This factor does not meet the required level; the gap is acknowledged and accepted given that the COU is restricted to the F1717 static protocol."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented mapping between experimental boundary conditions and FEA boundary conditions; differences quantified and shown to have <5% effect on QoIs.",
      "rationale": "Fixture compliance measured experimentally (k_fixture = 18,400 N/mm) and incorporated into FEA as a spring element at the load application point. Sensitivity analysis showed fixture compliance accounts for 2.1% of total stiffness; inclusion reduced QoI discrepancy from 8.4% to 6.3%."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
