    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted because the COU is explicitly scoped to the ASTM F1717 static compression-bending protocol and no multi-condition extrapolation is claimed. All three QoIs satisfy the pre-specified quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96; percentage difference < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is judged credible for its intended use in supporting the regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design.",
